hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: I’ve stayed here the last three times I’ve been in Paris and it always meets my expectations. The staff treats you very well, the location is perfect for any landmark and destination you want to visit in Paris and there’s a plethora of amazing restaurants within two blocks of the hotel. The rooms a very spacious and you have a view of the Eiffel Tower.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: I had the most incredible stay at Le Metropolitan, and it was primarily due to the head concierge, Kahina. From the moment I phoned to inquire about an early check-in (which she was able to accommodate) to the moment I checked out, Kahina provided the most unbelievable customer service. Every morning, my niece and I would head out for our da in Paris and Kahina was at the front desk inquiring how our previous day's adventures were, what was the plan for that day, and how could she help. Her knowledge of the area assisted us greatly. The location of this hotel is perfect. There are great restaurants all around. And at night, you have a beautiful view of the sparkly Eiffel Tower. If you are planning a trip to Paris, you will not go wrong booking this hotel.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
This is a Marriott?! No way -- this is an incredible boutique hotel with less than 50 rooms in a superb location. Oh, and you can see the Eiffel Tower by stepping out the front door.
Okay, the cons are that the rooms are unique and smallish, especially if you have a "Clam" style suitcase that opens in the middle. The other con is that hiccups happen -- such as a TV that comes on by itself and no remote for the TV in the room. However, the staff are extraordinary problem solvers who all speak perfect English. Must give a shout out to Kahina (concierge), Alina, and Stefan. Stefan went above and beyond to assist with printing (yes, paper printing) some tickets off cell phone. Merci, merci.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Great property in outstanding location.
Just wish few improvements are done for the property to be 5 star -
1) Air Conditioning - AC works only seasonally and our room felt a little hot, and opening window was not an option due to noise.
2) Breakfast - they offer two options for breakfast, as marriott platinums we received a complimentary continental breakfast (which didn't offer much), but if you would like to order eggs of your choice - you have to pay additionally for it. In my opinion both of those options should be combined.

Otherwise, it has same small rooms like in most hotels around Paris.
Front desk personnel were very attentive and helpful!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We paid big money for the Eiffel Tower suite and received a welcoming champagne bottle and letter from the General Manager, Marina Goyheneche. Unfortunately, the MAJORITY of amenities in this room were broken. The bathtub did not properly drain, nor did it fill up whatsoever; after complaining to the front desk via phone, we were told that they couldn't do anything about it and that they were well aware of the broken tub but that there wasn't anything they could do. The television had a huge dent and was utterly broken as well; again, we were told the same thing, they were aware, and there was nothing they could do about it. We spoke to the general manager upon checkout and were told that they were sorry for the broken amenities, which negatively impacted our stay in the top-floor Eiffel Tower Suite; however, there was nothing they could do about it. To say this was disappointing is an understatement. Yes, the view was phenomenal, but given these guys are charging a similar price to the Shangri-La with an even better view and renowned reputation for service, for The Eiffel Tower Suite, our stay in the suite was not all that we dreamed it would be. The manager either needs to work with better maintenance staff to fix these recurring issues right away, or she may need a replacement altogether for more effective and efficient staff. Not to take it to replace staff, but given how expensive the suite was, we were kicking ourselves for not noticing the broken amenities and the stained floors with enough time to check out and find alternative accommodation. I cannot speak to the rest of the hotel as we stayed in the best possible room and have significant complaints about the suite; I cannot imagine what other issues the rest of the hotel may have. Better yet, we found out that these guys are in partnership with Marriot Hotels or bought by them, so this could also explain the lack of care for their reputation and level of service. Unless you're looking for a basic room and a cute area, save your money on the suites here and go somewhere more reputable, like the Shangri-La. It'll set you back a similar price.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Great location, good room but unfortunately that’s where it ended for us.

Check-in - Smooth and somewhat personable, thanks to Stephane.

Room - we paid big $$$ for the Eiffel Tower suite and the view was definitely worth it. Room was a decent size for European standards.

Overall service - terrible experience with the gentleman who was working at the front desk on Saturday, 8 April (day shift). Called him for restaurant recommendations in Paris, his response ‘Sorry I am new here, I can’t give you any recommendations’ and proceeded to hang up !!! hmmm WTF !! I was furious, I don’t care how new you are, if you are not ready to provide a 5 star service, please don’t bother jumping behind the front desk ! I then called again and got told, ‘I am too busy with guests’, I asked if I can be put through the concierge and was subsequently transferred to a gentleman who wasn’t much help either. I asked if I could speak to the hotel manager, I was told ‘Madame is off today’ - whatever, please fool someone else. You are in the hospitality industry, representing a major brand !!!!!

The same afternoon, we requested an iron, which was broken and leaking water. When asked for the iron to be replaced, it never showed up.

We then asked if we could swim and/or use the steam, only to be told it was under maintenance that afternoon.

The bath in the suite takes almost an hour to fill up.

If you are someone who cares about details, don’t stay here. Staff need some serious training. I sum it up as a five star location with a two star service. The view itself was not worth the money I paid for.

Choose other Marriott options in Paris.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: My wife and just enjoyed five nights at the Le Metropolitan, Paris. We loved everything about it – location, the restaurant, the really cool grotto pool and our wonderful jr. Suite. We travel a lot and try to stay in hotels with character and style – the Le Metropolitan had both. Located in the 16th arrondissement close to the Eiffel Tower but tucked into a residential Paris neighborhood. Walkable to all the great Paris locations including little bistros and cafes. We will go back for its location, appropriate level of amenities but mostly because of the very professional and friendly staff. Tres Bein Le Metropolitan.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
I have been staying at this hotel since 2015 (back when it was a Radisson Bleu) and always feel like I am coming back to my home away from home whenever I visit. I love the location in the 16th near multiple metro stops in a fairly residential area of town near great food shops and a HUGE Casino grocery store.

This particular trip was short, so I did not spend a lot of time at the hotel. I arrived around 1pm and was told the room was not yet ready. Fortunately, it was expected to be ready within an hour (and an upgrade to a Deluxe Room!), and I was welcomed into the pool/spa area to rest, refresh, and relax while I waited. What a wonderful way to help overcome jetlag!

I always love seeing the Head Concierge, Kahina. It is because of her that I truly feel special and welcomed at this hotel. She goes out of her way to make sure that everything is perfect!

Superior and Deluxe rooms are on the small side, but at least with the Deluxe rooms you have a sizeable bathroom. The main reason I love staying at this hotel is the bed - it is one of the most comfortable beds I have ever slept in. I love the choice of bedding and the pillows are better than the ones I have at home. Rooms are kept clean and housekeeping is great; my only "complaint" on this trip was they had forgot to refill toilet paper and was running dangerously low; this was quickly remediated. Rooms have a small fridge and Nespresso machines with off brand nespresso pods. Bottles of Evian were also replaced everyday.

Breakfast continues to be a wonderful affair. The mini viennosieries are so yummy, and they serve some really high quality yogurt. Delicious butter, jams, and honey help to round out the experience, and there is a now a small buffet that is part of the continental breakfast that includes meats and cheeses; this is a nice addition.

It is funny to read some of the negative reviews here because I know that sometimes the hotel is not always perfect and American standards are not always in line with what European hotels deliver, but for me this hotel really is truly special.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Our visit didn't get off to a good start. We arrived to find the lobby filled with luggage and people waiting to check in. The front desk clerk (Orlando, I think?) was condescending and rude to us and other guests. We began to worry about our choice in hotels at this point. Fortunately, he was an anomaly at the hotel.

The rest of the hotel staff was very congenial and courteous. From Tareek, opening the front door to Jacinto and Suzanne serving us breakfast each morning and drinks in the afternoon, the service was wonderful. The housekeeping staff was continually maintaining the rooms and common areas. We can't say enough about Kahina at the hotel. She was a wealth of information about Paris and even greeted us by name by the second day of our stay.

The hotel restaurant (sushi & Asian) was fantastic. The location of the hotel is perfect. It is a short walk away from several major tourist attractions and short Uber/taxi ride to several others. The area restaurants, bars, and shopping were very nice and while the hotel is close to tourist areas, it was surprisingly quiet at night. The neighborhood felt very safe.

All of that said, there are a few areas that visitors need to be aware of. For one, the wifi is relatively slow and, most importantly, NOT a secure network. This is unacceptable to a contemporary traveling business person even with a VPN. Our television only worked part of the time and the housekeeping carts were left in the narrow hallways day and night.

The hotel is in need of a modernization or makeover to make it more contemporary - given the price of lodging. Perhaps the most problematic for us was that the room climate control NEVER worked. Every night was excessively warm and we were forced to open the window each night to obtain anything close to a comfortable temp. Of course, open windows led to more noise and very cold room temps when the outside temp dropped.

In all, this is a good hotel, with a very good staff, in an excellent location. More attention to technology, climate control, and modernization would make it perfect. We highly recommend Le Metropolitan.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: My family recently stayed at this hotel. The hotel was lovely and within walking distance of beautiful sights in Paris. I want to especially mention the incredible customer service. I accidentally left my bag behind at a restaurant the night before flying back to California. Kahina (head concierge) took personal time to pick up my bag and ship it back to me. I am so grateful for this kindness and would highly recommend a stay at this hotel.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We decided to splurge for our 40th wedding anniversary and stay at this very expensive Marriott. I mentioned the special occasion to the gentleman who checked us in and he said he'd give us a nice room. It was OK, good size for Paris, nice bed but that's all. No place for clothes except a small closet with a few hangers. No dresser, bureau or shelves etc. No luggage rack either. But the worst: No hot water in the shower!! We mentioned the next morning but nothing was done. And they wouldn't change our room. Mentioned again the following day, nothing again. I wrote to Marriott and got a letter from the general manager who said sorry but...

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
This hotel to me is home away from home, every time I plan a visit to Paris, this is my hotel.
The location is amazing, the Eiffel Tower Suites and the Deluxe Rooms with balcony and Eiffel Tower view are one of the most epic rooms you can find in Paris. The rooms are always clean

The location is walking distance to famous cafes as well as to the Eiffel Tower, also most of other attractions are close enough by taxi.

The Staff are super friendly and helpful, always ready to help and assist with everything.

I would like to thank Stephane, Osato from Front desk as well as Vanusa from the restaurant-Bar for their wonderful hospitality.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
- A hotel with a stupid reservation system (system bug)

- Very rude customer service

- Shame on you for being a member of the "Marriott Bonvoy"

- The brutality of blaming the hotel's fault on customers and travel agencies

- The smallest room can't even open a 30-inch carrier

I guess 3 stars hotel in downtown Paris has better service and better rooms

Plz go to this hotel if you want to get the customer service I mentioned above :(

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: My husband and I just returned from a 5 day stay at Le Metropolitan and it was simply amazing!! From the moment we checked in we knew we made the right choice. Stephane checked us in and he was so warm and welcoming, he knew it was our first time in Paris and upgraded us to room 517 with a beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower! Thank you Stephane!!Our daily breakfasts were delicious, pastries, fresh squeezed juice, coffee, cheese and fruit. The dining room area is very elegant and beautiful. We were served by Kevin daily and he was so so nice and helpful. There was another lady who also served us, I forget her name but she was so nice too! The hotel is the perfect location, close to the trocadero metro and very central. Honestly you can’t go wrong with this hotel truly a 5 star experience!! Yes the rooms are smaller but you’re in Paris, it’s expected! The rooms are spotlessly clean and very nice!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
We stayed for a weekend at Le Metropolitan in one of the suites and the experience has been amazing. I had asked the Concierge to prepare a surprise for my partner in the room and the team went above and beyond for everything.

We truly felt well taken care of during our stay thanks to the staff’s care and availability and will definitely visit again.

The suite was very nice with a beautiful view over the Eiffel Tower and the location was perfect for us.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
The team is fantastically helpful (big shout out to Kahina who took great care of me during my stay).
The hotel is so conveniently located near the subway and a quick minutes walk to Eiffel Tower. Make sure you book the room with the Eiffel Tower view - will not regret it at all! Highly recommended!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: I give this a hotel a three for the location but it is noisy at night so bring earplugs. The room is absolutely tiny and two of the three lamps do not work (no overhead lamps). The one in the corner even has no bulb. I have asked for assistance at the front desk twice in two days and now today I have the other bed side lamp working but not the main lamp in the corner. I have had to get ready to go out and go to bed the last two nights basically in the dark. I should not be this difficult. Also, the breakfast that is included in marginal. I’m surprised mariott includes this hotel.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Overall this hotel was disappointing and not a five star experience. Check-in went great and the staff was friendly and accommodating. As a titanium elite, I was hoping my suite night upgrades would clear, but they did not and we were not upgraded

We were assigned to a room with a king bed, with the shower/bathtub in the bedroom itself (less than 2 feet from the bed). There was also no curtain, which limits the rooms usage to any non-romantic guests. The shower itself had very high walls (over 2 feet) with no bars/handles to get in and out. On our first night, I slipped getting out of the bath due to the lack of non-slippery services and severely injured my leg. I messaged the hotel, they did not understand and told us they could Not switch our room. Understandable. I messaged again, saying I could no longer use the shower due to my leg and whether there was another room available. There was no response from them at all, even to indicate they were sold out.

The room is standard size for Europe, but a shower with no curtain/walls IN the room itself is too far. While the breakfast was great, the lack of response or concern from the hotel was disappointing. While I’ll be seeking medical attention, I won’t be returning to this hotel and I wouldn’t advise any group of more than 1 person to.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
It’s a beautiful hotel situated within walkable distance (10 minutes) to the iconic Eiffel Tower.
As I walk in, I felt like I was in a small museum. It was cozy and quiet. The decor is awesome. The room has an elegance and simpleness aura in it.
The bed is ultra comfortable that I felt in deep sleep within seconds. Maybe I was super tired, but the restful, deep sleep was definitely attributable to the quality of the mattress.
The Eiffel Tower lights up at the strike of dusk, it sparkles every 15 minutes after 11:00 PM.
We saw it several evenings right in front of our hotel.
Our room was super clean; the concierge was top notch. We couldn’t have a better service than Stephan who was always helpful, knowledgeable, courteous, and his command of English is very good. Stephan was instrumental in the success of our trip. There were no untoward incidents that happened at Hotel, everything was perfect from start to finish, all because Stephan was there to help every which way he could.
We will certainly go back. I’ve already told my relatives that Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel is the place to stay if they want pampered service, clean, beautiful location, cozy hotel.

Do not forget to order hot chocolate at the hotel. It’s the best hot chocolate I’ve ever had!
We thank Stephan for his professionalism and kindness, for his above par service.
We’re sad we had to check out.

Marilen V. and Josefina B.
Sept 21-25, 2022

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
This is a small hotel in the most perfect neighborhood with amazing views of the Eiffel Tower! The decor is modern, rooms are super clean, staff is amazing and location could not be better. I have officially found my go to Paris hotel and will definitely be back!

From the minute we walked in and talked to the team at the front desk everything was fabulous! They were so welcoming, recognized my Marriott status right away and did everything they could to make my stay perfect. We were fortunate enough to be upgraded to an Eiffel View suite thanks to my Ambassador status (and as a happy birthday from
the hotel team). It was even more amazing than the pictures. The rooms are not massive (no rooms are in Europe) but the location and views make up for it. It was amazing being able to lay in bed and see the Eiffel Towel sparkle at night! The room we were in had a lovely king bed, sitting area with a couch, two chairs, a table, and a small balcony!

They offer offsite parking for a fee and have a restaurant at the hotel that looked beautiful but we did not eat there!

I have stayed at several hotels in Paris and this is overall the best. The location/ price/ service are all fabulous for what you get. I can’t wait to return!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
We have just returned from a three night stay in this hotel. I had booked it months before and had emailed the hotel to inform them I was planning a proposal to my partner whilst in Paris and any upgrades or anything to make our stay extra special would be appreciated. They replied to say they would do their best subject to availability but would ensure I had a wonderful stay. I reflected and a week later I emailed to ask if there would be anything they could do to help assist me in a proposal eg decorate room etc…..I had no reply which to me is very poor service.
However when we arrived at the room and discovered how tiny it was, there was no way I would propose in there. The room was very dissappointing and nothing like the photos. I know Parisian hotels can be small but I didn’t like the fact the toilet was in a cupboard of its own and the shower and sink in a different area. The bathroom was grubby, with a drippy tap and mould on the ceiling. The room was boiling and air con wasn’t working. Not what you would expect of a five star hotel.

When we arrived at the hotel the check in was poor,no help or advice was given, and when asked if breakfast was included I was told no, I asked about coming to breakfast and the man on the desk said we would get a nice breakfast at a place down the road…..strange ( surely you would encourage guests to dine in the hotel)

A few days in( and after proposing without the hotels help) I spoke to kahina on the front desk who was lovely, and helpful and gave us a map of the city and the best places to go, I informed her of our proposal and she was very kind.
For a five star hotel I would have expected to return to the room to perhaps a congratulations slice of cake or glass of fizz or something to acknowledge such a life event….we returned to nothing. Having stayed in lower star hotels than this and being treated to complimentary bottles of fizz, the customer service this hotel is providing is extremely poor.
The only bonus is the location is central for Eiffel Tower and main tube lines. I would avoid booking here.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Perfect location to the museum and the river
Walk from hotels to shopping center and dinning
Underground parking hard to find
Good view friendly staff. Train and metro was across the street. Rent a small car make sure that you have working talking gps in the car

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
My partner and I were welcomed to the hotel by Karina who was super friendly, knowledgeable and helpful.
We were really happy to be upgraded to a room with an Eiffel Tower view, it made the stay very special, we loved to sit and watch the tower sparkle at night from our window.
As we visited in summer the air conditioning was welcomed, our room was kept cool all day and night.
We found the whole hotel to be spotlessly clean, we didn't get a chance to use the pool however but it looked amazing !!
Karina recommended great bakeries and restaurants for breakfast and dinner, both of which we loved and she also booked us great tickets for the sunset river cruise. The hotel is about a 10-15 minute walk from the Eiffel Tower and has 2 metro stations about a 5 minute walk away, which was perfect.
We will definitely return to the hotel !! Thank you !!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: It is almost illegal to call this hotel luxury. I am currently staying in Le Metropolitan and am astounded at how this hotel can be considered a 5 star hotel. The staff are very unknowledgeable and told us there wasn't a spa in the hotel when the website clearly states it. The room had multiple issues; an old smelly refrigerator, a leaking sink, and a broken phone that I couldn't even use. All were reported to the front desk. A night staff came to check on the leaking sink and never followed up to fix it. As a gold elite member I wasn't able to receive any perks and was not acknowledged for my loyalty. Each and every time we went to the front desk, they had no idea how to respond to a simple inquiry. We were clearly duped into staying at a 5 star hotel when this establishment feels nothing more than a 3 star hotel. The pictures are exaggerated and the rooms are so small that we couldn't even pass by the bed without bumping into each other. Not worth it especially after having to get a 20 minute cab ride every time we wanted to go to the main area.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Booked this hotel about 3 months in advance of my honeymoon. I emailed the reservations desk about the importance of my trip and to stress that I am a gold Marriott member / AMEX platinum holder , so i was hoping that there would be an upgrade available (although I am fully aware that is not guaranteed). At the MINIMUM, I would have expected a decent room since I booked the queen room and notified the hotel months in advance.

Upon arrival, I was told that they were fully committed so no upgrade (upsetting but no problem). We get into the room , which mind you was in the BACK of the hotel and facing a dumpster. This is the kind of treatment I get after booking so long in advance and kindly asking to be taken care of given it was my honeymoon. The room was tiny and looked like a knock off version of the pictures that are in the website.

To top this all off, there was construction so loud that the room was shaking. I was so upset , I came downstairs to complain and demand a room change. Of course they could not do that and were shocked that I complained about construction after a 7 hour flight and that I was the only guest to do so. I immediately called Marriott and cancelled my reservation and switched hotels. When I came downstairs , there were other people also checking out and complaining about the construction.

This hotel is horrible, the location is horrible and the rooms look nothing like they do in the pictures. Stay far away!!!! I never leave reviews because I don’t wish to give a negative image on a business but this was so disrespectful and upsetting on my honeymoon that I had too.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
I stayed one night with my young son. This a pleasant small hotel on a quiet place just a few minutes from the Eiffel Tower. The staff are very professional and friendly, and all seemed to speak English quite well (I speak ok French, but sometimes need to fall back on English when discussing travel logistics, etc.) Our room (their least expensive, I think) was small but the beds were very comfortable, and there was even a little Parisian balcony.

I will say that the hotel, probably like most in Paris, seemed to just be getting back on its feet from Covid. They were a bit short-staffed at the front desk (but always very polite). The indoor pool was also in a bit of disarray thanks to ongoing repairs from some previous flooding.

The neighborhood, in the 16th arrondissement, is lovely but very touristy. In the summer you will probably hear as much English as French on the streets. But it’s a fine jumping off point if you want to see Paris. The hotel also seemed well-equipped for business travelers (good WiFi, helpful staff, etc.)

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
This hotel is pure Parisian spirit.
The location, a stone's throw from the Tour Eiffel and the Trocadero.
The building, a classy 19th century French style structure.
The hotel itself, so cozy and delicate and romantic.
The hall and the reception, so stylish.
The rooms, very comfortable and clean.
The breakfast, very good and savory.
Above all, however, stands the staff of this hotel. Professional, customer-oriented, helpful yet warm, friendly and cheerful.
Madame Kahina, the Front Office Manager, is pure professionality and style but always ready to share a joke or a laugh thus making your stay even more delightful.
Do not miss the chance to stay at the Metropolitan when in Paris. You'll regret if you didn't.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
It’s a hotel far over priced with the service and the size of the room
Despite I am the top tier of the Bonvoy member the service quality I have received is really poor
We booked three rooms with one suit and none of the rooms are available prior 3 pm despite our request on the app and call for a early check in

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: I stayed in this hotel in the latter part of June and found it to be fantastic. Are the rooms small? Absolutely, the smallest I have ever seen. Once you get over that and realize that you are in Paris for hopefully, more than the hotel room, you can really start to enjoy yourself. I found the staff to be charming, professional and helpful. This is a small hotel and appeared to be filled with Marriott Elite members (of which I am one) who have booked a holiday using points and who expect their room to be ready when they land at CDG in the morning (check in at 3 pm), a full American breakfast with bacon and eggs and an upgrade (there are only 48 rooms in the hotel and the larger rooms are first allocated to guests who have actually paid for these rooms). I applaud the staff for their poise. We enjoyed our stay immensely. Also, we noted no issues with the air conditioning.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
The reasons for the 1 star:
- rude management - very dismissive when asked about an upgrade. Paying over $1K a night with the highest bonvoy level, called before booking and after, mentioned special occasion. Got nothing. I asked for 1 night only upgrade, still nothing.
- breakfast - we should’ve skipped it. Not worth it and the staff are really stiff! I’ve studied and worked here in Paris and I know the system very well, so it’s not the Parisian way of things, it’s just them! I think they are just overworked and that’s why they’re short with customers especially if someone who just checked in asks about the continental vs the full breakfast
- super small rooms even in Paris standards

I think the hotel has a lot of potential if the management team changes or they change their approach. I felt that some of the staff aren’t too happy with management or how things are ran but as a customer that’s not my issue.

Another disappointing experience with Marriott BonVoy ambassador level. Really inconsistent and having to “negotiate” with every hotel for what we need, weather it’s a room with twin beds, or a simple upgrade (not suits!!), or high floor even though we are calling the hotels before and after booking to make sure as well as noting our requests in the reservation itself. I’ve already re-earned Ambassador Dor next year but really stays like this one at the Le Metropolitan makes me re-question my loyalty to this brand and this program.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: People at the reception were great and helpful. However this is not a luxury hotel. Aside from being close to the Eiffel Tower, there is not much good about this hotel. Below Marriott standards. Rooms are dated and small. No air conditioning so be aware traveling in summer. Additionally, the restaurant staff was very rude and unaccommodating. We were sitting in a 2 person table, and my 13 year old daughter came down to sit with us and we wanted to pull up a chair, they got all flustered and upset. By the way, restaurant was empty. One more table beside us. For this price, look elsewhere.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Ridiculously small room, even for Parisian standard
Wifi super slow - unusable
Minibar empty
Only 2 small bitter of water in the room
Bed uncomfortable
We paid 495€ for all of the above.
Ok we are in Paris - and not even in the center of Paris - but this place is a (bad) joke!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
The hotel manager was a SCAM!!!
Please be careful… she charged me wrong a amount and told me she will fix it. Its been more than 2 months that i have tried to get my money back, she never replied.
She sent an email telling Marriot that i tried to make a scene at the front desk.
Her attitude when she was talking to me on the day of my arrival was bad, she acted like she’s superior than me, acting like she is only right, never accepts her mistake and most importantly she RAISED her voice to me, which is unacceptable.
Nimit Manatpon
Stayed on March 22nd 2021

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Booked two nights at this place with our Marriott loyalty points, we were not informed there is no AC in the entire building until we called front desk. Our room was 85 degree and felt like sauna.
We have to cancel our stay due to the AC issue, and Marriott guaranteed we will be getting our points back... still haven't received anything.. will not return again.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: The room was advertised as having air conditioning. However, our suite did not have air conditioning and we paid full price, and were not offered any discount for not having and air conditioning. Room was very hot.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We loved our stay at this beautiful hotel and we are definitely hoping to come back someday! The staff were so friendly and helpful. They were kind, welcoming and gave us great advice. The room was beautiful, with balcony views of the eiffel tower! So magical! The room was small but still plenty of space. It was perfectly clean and well maintained. The location was fantasic with a great neighborhood and plenty of restaurants nearby. The pool was a wonderful way to relax after a long day of walking around Paris.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: The Eiffel View Suite is exquisite. I cannot imagine a more perfectly Parisian view. Plus, the sitting area and bedroom area are separated by doors in case you’re traveling with someone and want a little extra privacy. We arrived during an unseasonably cold snap, but they’d already turned off the heat to the building, so they delivered a space heater that warmed up the room in minutes. Also, the room service breakfast was lovely and delivered quite quickly. Overall, a great experience. 10/10 would recommend.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Stayed here for 4 nights recently. Lovely modern hotel,fabulous Eiffel Tower views from every room. Super helpful staff always willing to help with queries quickly and efficiently. Room comes with robe and slippers and a choice of pillows. Recommend

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Not good value for money. For €425 rate not including breakfast, there are better options are out there.
The location is a plus, but the room was extra small, there was no concierge in the hotel on a Saturday, and the breakfast was very average for Paris. Will look elsewhere next time.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Only got to stay one night, but the hotel is great. Extremely friendly and helpful staff, amazing peak-a-boo view of the Eiffel Tower and great location. The rooms are small, providing what you need for a comfortable stay...perfect for those that spend most of their time out in the city of Paris. Highly recommend!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: The staff at this hotel are outstanding. So professional and handle stress with a smile. While this hotel recently reopened and they had some issues, their staff was beyond accommodating. The location is fantastic. You can see the Eiffel Tower outside the front door. But I can’t say enough about their staff. Top notch.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
So in the height of this COVID-19 drama, we have had to look at moving our wedding. That meant moving our honeymoon too. We booked this hotel for our last night in Paris through Hotels.com - which I will never use ever again!

Hotels.com refused to even consider changing the booking even though the hotel has a policy for refunds before 30 June. We reached out to the hotel for help- and Sarah was amazing! She managed to sort the booking out for us.

This hotel clearly values its clientele and honours it’s booking agreement. We are thinking about staying for even longer after this level of assistance, and will ONLY book direct with the hotel and NEVER with hotels.com again. We can’t wait to stay here, Sarah has helped relieve a huge part of the stress of moving a wedding for me, and she should be recognised for her amazing work!

Thank you Sarah!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We had to end our stay 2 nights early due to COVID-19 and this hotel was extremely flexible and understanding; we didn’t have to pay for the late cancel. Incidentally, the staff was also very friendly when we first checked in. Sometimes Americans think Parisians are unfriendly but that wasn’t our experience of Paris at all, especially not this hotel staff. Quite the opposite. We can’t wait to go back, and Le Metropolitan will be at the top of our list next time as well.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
This hotel should have its Marriot association stripped. And be turned into a motel not a hotel.

I have never ever in my life seen more hostile staff that even after staying for a full week were still rude.

If I ask any question I would recieve attitude as if I was begging them for help. They are clearly have no idea or any clue what hospitality is.

The concierge is worthless.

I asked her for a place where I can find socks she started haffing and puffing then after an hour told me to go to a store that didn’t have any socks.

Thats just one example.

I can go on and on.

Il spare you tho and recommend that you spare yourself the night mare of staying here.

If you want to see the Eiffel Tour you know you can go walk up to it for free right?

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Only positive point is the location, this hotel clearly needs a management reshuffle.
For the budget ( about 300 euros per night, you have much better options in the same location) ,
I spent there 2 nights, room was EXTRA small and cleanliness was not ideal.
Also first day i came back at 430 pm and the room was still not cleaned...
Service is really bad, spent an hour in the bar without anyone inquiring if i needed anything, hotel to be avoided.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: This truly was one of the smallest hotel rooms I have had, and by far not the cheapest! There was no place for my medium sized suitcase, which had to be placed on my bed during the day and behind the door at night. What was most disappointing were the stains on the floor and the damaged and scratched walls and furniture, albeit that the bed was ok. There was no desk, just a 20 cm deep shelf mounted against the wall with a chair. Breakfast was ok, but rather slow. The location was convenient, close to the Eiffel tower; however, noisy at night. The bathroom (or shower cell) window curtains are see-through. Nice staff though.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: I had a excellent stay in this Boutique hotel. Great first impression in the classy lobby which has a cozy bar area with a beautiful fireplace. The front office team was so friendly and professional! I really loved my room, especially the side view of the Eiffel Tower! The pool/hammam area is a big plus, especially in Paris, where it's not common! Very good hotel.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Front desk staff made me feel welcome and were very friendly and helpful. This hotel is close to many attractions including the Eiffel Tower. Our room was ready early and was very clean. Hotel staff were all helpful.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
5* Service, very clean comfortable and modern room, beautiful view, very friendly staff at the reception, nice SPA and pool, top location.
One of the best hotel I have visited in Paris.
Highly recommended

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Spent two nights at this boutique hotel and it was a great experience. The staff is very professional et cordial. Particularly Sarah at the front desk who was highly professional during check in and check out, she made the experience pleasant as soon as I walked through the front door.

Decoration at the hotel is classy, rooms despite being small (typical in Paris), are very clean with beautiful design.

Nespresso machine in the room and bath robes are pleasant to have after long walks out. Location is just amazing.

The only missing detail is a doorman to open the door for clients since doors are not automatic. It will make the experience even more warm for clients with baggages more so because taxis and Ubers cannot park properly given the presence of the roundabout.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: First time here, great location as it is just 10-15 mins walk to Tour Eiffel. There’s a bakery shop nearby “Le Grenier a Pain” selling amazing pastries, and they start business very early! Though we got a complimentary upgrade to Suite but there’s no Club Lounge. Overall the experience is good!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Loved this hotel, its very Parisian and short walking distance to the Eiffel tower. I hate to find out the size of the regular rooms, from reading other reviews I opted for the a suite. Its a must if you are traveling with more than one person.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: .... the rooms were overheated and the temperature control did not work. This seems to be a known problem and we were not the only ones to complain, the temperature was at 25 Celsius (80 f) all the time which is too hot to sleep well. They seem to have e spent a lot of money on the renovation so it’s a pity they could not get something basic right but it is an issue in winter when cold.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
This is a very small hotel, in a residential neighborhood. The entrance is sophisticated with nice fireplaces and seating area. Really liked the neighborhood.
Pros: Walking distance to Eiffel, small shops and grocery stores very close; Rooms are well appointed with bathrooms nice sized with place to spread out toiletries. Nice amenities. Nespresso in room with plenty of capsules. Nice staff. Robes in rooms. Property is well maintained.

Cons: A/C and heat difficult to figure out and the room wasn't ever comfy (perhaps me); Bathroom doors swing and can't be propped open and the rooms aren't very quiet. Everytime our neighbor came the doors opening and closing were super loud. Beds are so/so and sheets mediocre. No plugs next to bed so charging phones away.

Unless you get the star room with view of Eiffel, you view other apartments. My wake up call came one hour early - totally annoying.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
What a wonderful hotel, and great staff. Right in the heart of Paris, a great view of the Eiffel Tower, which is only a 5 minute walk away.

The staff is very nice and helpful. The hotel is modern, clean and welcoming. Great area on the first floor to have a drink and sit by the fireplace. Tons of great restaurants around as this is not a tourist area. And, great shopping. A bakery and grocery around the corner too.

Thanks to Kahina, who booked all our site seeing tours, my wife and I had a wonderful time!

We will be back again in 2020 as you cannot beat the location, staff and amenities'.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Had the pleasure of staying here couple years ago. Went for the Eiffel suite view after seeing a couple photos on instagram. Ended up making a iphone video snippet of the bed and view of the tower and it went viral as top hotel video of the year. Extremely happy with my stay everyone should visit at one point in there life :D

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We really enjoyed our stay. The room and service was excellent especially Kahina was very helpful and friendly. The location is also great with a secret street full of little French shops. Strongly recommend!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: My husband and I had the chance to combine a work and personal trip to Paris recently and absolutely had the nicest stay at Le Metropolitan. The rooms are beautiful and comfortable, the pool is an extra treat and the location on Place de Mexico is in one of our favorite neighborhoods in Paris. The staff (thank you, Kahina!) was super helpful throughout our stay, particularly when I lost an earring under a closet which they were able to retrieve and mail back to me. We are already looking forward to our next stay at Le Metropolitan.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: This is my second time staying on this hotel and both times have always been a pleasure. The very top Paris Suite is the most sought after simply because of its stunning view of the Eiffel Tower most esp when its lit up at night. I would just sit in my couch as I watch it glow. The staff are also very gracious and nice some of them more knowledgeable about certain things than the others but I can see that they all try their best! I would not hesitate to stay here again and again when Ill be back in the city of lights.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: This is the best kept secret in Paris... Amazing location ... 1 block away from Trocadero and subway :) which mean the Eiffel Tower is right facing the hotel in the plaza ... Still closet to Champs-Élysées . shopping ... .Victor Hugo local restaurants and more local shopping ... Grocery store and bakery a few steps away ... I have been in Paris many times and this is my favorite hotel to stay ... Location , service, food, rooms are beautiful and the bedding and pillows love them... If you can spare the money and have a room with the view of the Eiffel tower best money ever expend ... You will have the must amazing Eiffel tower sunrise ever and your own Eiffel Tower light show every hour from the privacy and comfort of sofa or bed in your room ... If it is your first time in Paris please take in consideration hotel rooms and bathrooms in Paris are pretty small ...

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Stayed for three nights in the 3rd floor Eiffel View Suite. The room offfered a fantastic straightaway view of the Eiffel , which looked great all lit up in the evening. Since it was a suite, the room was a great size, with a separate living area. It was separated from the bedroom area by a movable wall which opened if you slide it . It was a very unique and good idea, and we kept it both opened and closed depending on if we wanted to see the view from bed, or from the couch. the shower and tub room was great and the toilet was in a little room off by itself near the room door. I actually thought this is a great idea, and wish more hotels had it. The complimentary breakfast was OK, but nothing special like other hotels in Europe offer.
The staff was friendly and attentive, although they did forget to reserve a restaurant for us one night , after being assured that they would. But luckily when we got to the restaurant, they were able to fit us in.

All in all, I recommend staying there and would stay there again when back in Paris.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: In Paris for my daughter’s wedding, stayed August 22-25th the room was small but efficiently organized and had all the amenities. The staff was so helpful and accommodating for all our needs especially, Sarah who was amazing, she went above and beyond to help make our stay stress free, my daughter needed her wedding dress pressed, Sarah not only found a cleaners to press it, but had the dress returned in just hours! The location of the hotel is central and close to many restaurants and historical sites, the view of the Eiffel Tower from the hotel at night was breathtaking. Several family members present and we all stated we would love to stay at the hotel again, highly recommend Le Metropolitan in Paris

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Stayed 4 nights from August 18-22. Booked a standard room with 2 single beds and had read many reviews before booking. Yes the room was quite small but it had all the amenities that one would expect from a nice boutique hotel. There was a mini fridge which I had them empty so I could use for our own snacks and drinks, a Nespresso maker which makes espresso sized coffee fyi (very good coffee, you better like it strong!), slippers, robes, shampoo/conditioner/shower gel/body lotion, hair dryer, safe. As others have mentioned it was a bit odd to have the watercloset on the opposite side of the room from the sink and shower but it was fine. I would say if you are a larger person the bathroom may be an isssue for you. The shower stall size was large enough for sure, but the space outside the shower to get changed was very small and there is a giant window, well covered by a curtain, but seemed a little odd to have right there in the shower area. The room was very clean and comfortable. The phone is a mobile that you can use freely and even make phone calls back to Canada, the USA, anywhere in Europe for free! Mine unfortunately was in need of some updates they couldn't do onsite so although it was supposed to have free data to use around town mine didn't work. Not the end of the world, but probably the only disappointment I had with my stay. The front desk staff as others have mentioned were genuinely friendly and very helpful. They were all nice, but Sarah stood out to me as the most friendly and helpful. The location of the hotel was brilliant, about 5 minutes walking from the Trocadero stop on the metro. You could walk to the Eiffel Tower in about 10 minutes and the Arc de Triomphe in about 15-20. There were many restaurants within easy walking distance. There is a covered market just accross the street with 2 bakeries, a wine shop, a few take away restaurants and a Casino grocery store which I visited daily for snacks and drinks. Travelled with my 12 year old son and felt the neighbourhood was quite safe, we walked back from the metro in the dark a couple of times later at night and felt comfortable. I would definately stay here again and recommend this hotel.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
We really enjoyed returning to Paris and staying in a new area. The Staff is very friendly and extremely helpful as well.

It's a smaller boutique hotel and you can't be the walkable location. We only had breakfast there one morning but it was very good and our service was great as well.

I can recommend this hotel. Nice to walk about on your balcony with views of the Eiffel Tower especially at night.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Goodness, such a lovely looking hotel building in a very central quarter. I'm always amazed how architects and designers maximise the space available to them, especially where the price of real estate is stratospheric... so is the hotel small....yes, are the rooms small.... obviously and the architects have worked hard to make it all work but an epic fail in my book would be the toilet (booth) being in the opposite corner to the bathroom and the bathroom being so small anybody over 250lbs would have to walk in and back out ( we didn't have that problem) but there was only enough space for one person in the shower-room/bathroom. As room was booked by our friends under a family discount scheme so we really couldn't complain due to the considerable price discount we enjoyed. We were out all day and most nights so really only used the room for sleeping. However we would recommend if booking in future asking to view the room before accepting and if not happy asking for a larger room.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: This was our first stay here on a one night stopover and our junior suite was upgraded to the 5th floor with Eiffel Tower view! Nice! We like the Trocadero area which is why we booked here and were pleased. The front desk staff both arriving and departing were friendly and helpful. The breakfast was also fine. Our one night was in the middle of the heat wave so the AC could not keep up. They did supply a fan which helped. I am sure it is much better in normal weather. sadly the construction down the Rue blocked some of the Tower.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Iverall a great stay. Excellent staff and such a grest location. Our room was exceptional. Really wss beyond our expectations. Our only issue was the air conditioning was not operating properly during our stay. The front desk wss very empathetic. As it wss beyond their control, they offered us in room amenties, fans, water etc...to lighten the heat! As a gesture of good faith, the hotel awarded us 2 nights of Marriott reward points for that class of hotel. We were beyond plessed. We will be back.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
When we travel, we do our research and read reviews. So I feel like I need to set the record straight with this hotel. I was so excited about it and the views of the Eiffel Tower that people posted.

The reality was that we received a room the size of broom closet - literally there was no where to even set our suitcase down to unpack and I could hit my husband's feet when walking next to the bed. Honestly, I don't think the Marriott elite status means anything here. Just a heads up on that.

I'm not trying to trash this hotel - for those lucky enough to get the suites with the amazing views, I'm so envious. I just want to set the record straight for others doing research and expecting that amazing trip to Paris.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We stayed at this hotel for 3 nights from June 28 through June 31st nights. Excellent location in between Arc De Triomphe and Eiffel Tower. Very good people and customer service. However, the room we had (Deluxe Room with one king bed) was very very small. There was hardly any space to put our baggage. Our room was on the 6th floor.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We arrived after a long day of travelling. Easy to find boutique hotel with short access to Eiffel Tower, the Seine, Arc de Triumph, etc. Guest services was most accommodating, quickly, professionally signing us in, remembering our names over our 4 day visit, providing suggestions and guidance for our itineraries and adventures. BTW the staffs English is excellent and they are friendly. Location is excellent, a couple of blocks from the Eiffel Tower, museum of man, the Seine, The Boutique style has all the services without the mob scene of a large chain hotel in a historical craft style accomadation.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We stayed here for several days and the hotel and staff were great. It’s close to several restaurants and coffee shops. We walked everywhere to see all the sites. If you go to Paris, we recommend you check out this place.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Location is perfect. Just 5 mins walk from Trocadero Metro Station. 7 mins walk from Chaillot Palace, so close to tour eiffel.
Room was absolutely clean, bedding was very comfortable and the staff was all welcoming and nice.
This room was most sweet and romantic hotel suite I have ever been to.
I am recommending this hotel to everyone who is willing to visit Paris.
Even if you don't stay in tour eiffel view suite, the hotel is worth visiting in location-nice staff-clean room-nice interior-wise.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
We were in Paris for ten days and stayed
at the Le Metropolitan. I cannot speak more
highly of the entire staff, especially for
Ms.Kahina Abderrahmane , who is the
Concierge/Front desk. She was remarkable,
extremely knowledgeable and made our
stay all the more enjoyable.
The Hotel is in a good location, close to
the Eiffel Tower and restaurants. The rooms are clean, comfortable and have a great air conditioning system ! A nice breakfast is served in the morning. After a day of sightseeing we relaxed in the hotel pool
and sauna. I would most definitely
reccomend staying here.

 Concierge / Front desk

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Loved the location of this hotel. This was my second time in Paris. Short walk to the Eiffel Tower, the Arc de Triomphe, the train station and shopping on the Champs-Elysées. This is considered the Trocadero area. The hotel staff was very, very nice and helpful. This included the front desk personnel, the bar staff and housekeeping. We had some travel issues coming from the states and we arrived very early and our requested room wasn't ready but they let us check in to another room just to take a nap while out room was getting ready. Very much appreciated. Can't beat the view of our requested room either from the walk out balcony......a perfect view of the Eiffel Tower.
Loved the spiral staircase and the afternoon sitting area for cocktails.
The rooms are very small though, other than that, we thoroughly enjoyed our stay here.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Stylish, cozy property with friendly and helpful staff. While our room was small it was comfortable, and depending on your Paris plans, the location is good. The staff suggested a great Moroccan restaurant and arranged for tickets to Giverny. The breakfast was modest, yet elegant and healthy. I would stay there again - great for a brief city visit.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
I'm not one to give a really bad review (check out my profile and you will see I don't) but this was not a good hotel. I have Titanium status with Marriott which means I've stated at a lot of Marriotts and some of their Tribute hotels too. We booked this on points almost a year ago because Marriott was going to raise the category to a 6 for this hotel and we wanted to stretch our points while it was still a category 5. Really, Marriott? This is not a category 5 and should have never been upgraded to a 6.

When we arrived the front desk person was quite pleased to inform us that we had been upgraded because of status. Once we saw the room, we knew it couldn't possibly be an upgrade. It is the smallest room we have ever had anywhere even by European standards. There was no chair, no desk and nowhere to put luggage (and we travel light!) We finally squeezed the suitcase in the armoire because there was no room elsewhere. My husband and I are not big people but we had to walk sideways to get around the room. There was only a small bench (about 10 inches wide) that had the coffee pot.

The room was done in black marble. Might have sounded good on paper but made the room and bathroom seem even smaller. There were no hooks in the room to hang anything. We came back wet one day after being caught in the rain and had no place to hang wet clothes. We couldn't hang them in the armoire because our suitcase was in there and the wet clothes would have dripped on the clean clothes.

There was also no mirror in the bedroom and the bathroom was so small, two people couldn't fit in there to get ready in the morning. Every other place we stayed had a mirror in the bedroom so I could be putting on make-up and getting ready while my husband was showering. The design was an attempt to make the hotel look artsy and more like a boutique property. However, the rooms ended up not being user friendly. If you are going to have rooms that small add a few touches to help the customer.

However, our biggest issue was cleanliness. There was no top sheet on our bed; all we had to pull over us was a comforter that looked like it hadn't been cleaned in a while. The bare floor was obviously dirty when the sun shined in the room. I dropped a bar of soap in the shower and it left a white ring on the black marble. The ring stayed there for two days which obviously told us the shower had not been wiped down. Same with the bathroom sink; there were spots on the sink that we had to wipe down every day when we came back so obviously cleaning people were not wiping down the room properly.

The public bathroom down by the restaurant also was not cleaned on a regular basis. I stopped in there after breakfast the first morning rather than heading back to the room before we ventured out and I noticed that there were two open small bars of soap. I went in again the third morning and the open soap was still there and both bars were quite dirty at that point as was the sink. Who puts open bars of soap in a public bathroom? I told the front desk it needed to be cleaned.

I confirmed prior to coming that we would get the breakfast because of status. When we arrived, I was told I would have to give up the 1,000 point welcoming gift to get the continental breakfast. it's never been an either, or situation with Marriott so was quite surprised at that. We chose the breakfast since we were planning on it and wish we had kept the points instead. The breakfast was the most pathetic breakfast we had on our entire trip. It consisted of a small jar of yogurt and the same few pastry selections every day -- and they normally charge 25 euros for that! I asked one day if I could get some fruit and the hostess was so put out by my request that I didn't ask again. For anyone planning to stay there, don't waste your points or your money; simply go down the street to another place.

I gave it a 2 star rating only because the front desk staff, for the most part, were very good and location is great. I simply would not recommend this hotel, even with the good location. There are too many choices in Paris to settle for this one.

Marriott, if you are going to look for Tribute hotels to align with look at Greenmount House in Dingle, Ireland or Kilkenny Hiberian Hotel in Ireland. Both are lovely boutique hotels that had every amentity. But please don't try to convince me that Le Metropolitan should be a category 6. I've stayed at Fairfields that were much cleaner and nicer than this property.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
The location of Le Metropolitan is fantastic. The 16th district is one of the best in the city, and many wonderful cafes and shops are close by. And, the Eiffel Tower is literally a 5 min walk away- awesome!! The hotel is extremely clean, safe and modern.

That being said, be warned that the rooms in this hotel are VERY small, unless you are able to get a Junior Suite. We had a classic room. We were traveling for 2 weeks so had large suitcases. There is no place to store them in a classic room. And I mean NO place. So, we had to stack them against one of the walls when not in use, but still ended up tripping over them or having to jump over them to cross from one side of the room to another. There is a closet, but it's teeny, with room to only hang a couple of items. It's odd too, b/c the rod to hang clothes is mid-way down in the closet, so longer items bunch up at the floor. The bathroom is also very small. You basically have to shimmy your way in and out sideways to get to the toilet. We were two people in the room and it was crammed. We constantly had to maneuver around each other and map out who was doing what on what side of the room when.

Again, lovely hotel, just know what you're getting yourself into space-wise ahead of time. And DO NOT buy breakfast at the hotel. You'll pay over 30 euro for a basket of bread and coffee. Instead, hop right out of the front door and visit one of the many bakeries and coffee shops close by. Paul (bakery/coffee) was our favorite!!!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
This is a small boutique hotel well situated near the Eiffel Tower and Metro.
Our room was clean and spacious by Paris standards- king size bed. We had dinner one night in the restaurant - it was delicious, try the fish if available. There is a pool in the basement. We had a very good experience at this property.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We based ourselves in this part of Paris, as we wanted to explore the not so touristy part of the city but at the same time wanting somewhere a little posh and close to Eiffel. We stayed here for 4 nights and had the Eiffel-view suite. Note that the top floor suite is called Eiffel suite and costs a little more. The hotel has a boutiquey feeling with extensive use of wood, marble stone and steel. We liked the Carita brand toiletries and found they are much better quality than the average ones you get. Bedding is superb, probably one of the best we had during our 3-week trip. We used the metro extensively and you have the choice of either Victor Hugo and Trocadero. Both about 10-mins stroll. We also enjoyed the amenities around and given it's in the suburbia, you also get easy access to supermarket, takeaway shops, cafes, boulengeire, restaurants, atms etc. Now, if you don't like noise, you may have to avoid this hotel as it's bordered by two streets and a roundabout in front of the hotel. It can get busy and noisy and we do notice it in the morning and occasionally at night (after 10pm). However, the plus side is you get a glimpse of Eiffel if you book any of suites (although somewhat blocked by the current construction from another hotel). Special mention to Efim who look after us with our special request during our stay.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: The wife and had a one night layover if Paris. The Le Metropolitan is located perfectly for walking around the city and seeing some of the main sites. Very close to the Water Taxi. Could not have asked for a better view from the room. The staff was so very nice. The only bad part is that we only had one night to stay there.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We stayed there for one night, the service was great however the rooms were very small. The bathroom and shower are separate, the bathroom is tiny, the shower was a bit larger, we hardly had space to move around in the room.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
I found this hotel on Instagram (I know, I know, but hear me out), and the photos of the Eiffel Suites sold me. I am so glad they did!

That said, although the rooms/property look great in the photos, in-person the Eiffel Suite is even better.

Imagine your balcony door swung open to the sounds of the city during the day, and the sparkling lights of the Eiffel Tower at night.

The room was clean and BIG. Great bathroom, too!

The staff was incredibly kind and efficient.

This is a bargain for the location, room size, view, and incredible staff.

Book. It. Now.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We had a junior suite and it was perfect for two people The rooms were compact but well appointed, the shower nice and spacious, the soaker tub was a welcome surprise after a trans-Atlantic flight, bed was comfy. The hotel restaurant holds it own in a culinary capital and we enjoyed a breakfast and dinner while staying. All the staff were friendly and helpful. Love the 16th Arrondissement and the hotel is perfectly situated for walkability to metro, venues, restaurants, and just plain wandering with happy feet. This is a location for returning to as our Paris main base again and again.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Amazing in every way. Great location, far from tourist hubs, but close enough to everything. Their restaurant is a true find. Small hotel,very discreet. Close to many michelin star restaurants. Will definetely return. We always walk, loved discovering the neighborhoods around the hotel.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
I stayed here on a 13 hour layover. I came in around 1130 pm and left at around 9am.

Check-in was easy and the staff was very friendly and helpful. They were good to great me in the mornings. When I checked out and was waiting for my Uber they came over to see if I needed assistance. Now this is service.

The room I got was nice. I didn't get the upgrade I was sort of expecting but the room was nice none the less. It was smaller (it's Paris) and the toilet was separate from the sink but I managed. The little terrace you could step out onto and see the Eiffel Tower.

It's in great walking distance to the metro station and to the Eiffel Tower. This is a nice neighborhood. In fact, on my place ride out, the man I sat next to lives in this neighborhood and said I had made a great choice. If only I were there longer...

Next time!!!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
My wife and I traveled to Paris for our first time and decided to stay at Le Metropolitan; it did not disappoint.

The hotel is very well hidden amongst the residential buildings of the 8th ARR, which add a very local feeling to your stay. It's a small boutique hotel with English speaking staff that offers a small swimming pool in the basement, a steam room and spa services and an award winning restaurant that serves fantastic food at reasonable prices given food prices in Paris.

Room sizes are typical European sizes with a separate toilet and shower area and two twin beds were pushed together to create a queen bed. We found with two carry on luggage's and 2 checked luggage's the space was a little tight, but it did not feel uncomfortable.

Complimentary use of the in room Nespresso machine was a nice touch with refill pods provided daily. Additionally the complimentary cell phone provided by the hotel offers guests the ability to make local calls for free and and LTE data (which is helpful if you have the Paris Metro App), although we found it slow and opted for a tourist SIM card from Orange. The daily water bottles provided helped us when walking the street of Paris.

Guests can take comfort in knowing that there is a grocery store less than 2 mins walk (200M) from the hotel if they want to make food, buy water, or alcohol.

Trocadero Metro station is less than a 10 min walk from the hotel and is a great Metro station that has many direct lines to popular tourist destinations.

Major tourist attractions like the Eiffel Tower, Arc de Triomphe, Champs-Elyees, Palais de Tokyo are all largely with a 10-20 min walk from the hotel, most of which is downhill.

The neighbor is safe and well lit with people walking around at all hours, we felt comfortable walking back to the hotel from late night drinks at 1230AM.

All in all, this is a great hotel within walking distance of many tourist attractions. Its proximity to the Metro make getting around Paris simple. We easily come back and stay at Le Metroplitan again.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We stayed for two nights in the Eiffel Tower view room. It was very nice and clean. The staff was extremely helpful and kind. Definitely worth the stay. Close to everything you want to do. Only about a 15 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: I would definitely stay here again on a future trip to Paris. It is an easy walk to the Trocadero and the Eiffel tower. Three of us walked there from the Arc de Triomphe also. There is a market in a nearby building that has a great selection of groceries and wine. We had a view of the Eiffel tower from our rooms which was a treat. The staff were friendly. The hotel was very comfortable, although yes the rooms are small by US standards.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: The service at the front desk was what really stood out about this hotel. They were extremely helpful and friendly. I had a junior suite which had a separate sitting area. Friends had a smaller single room (small based on US standards). The bed was very comfortable. The continental breakfast was enough food for me (cost €20). There was a larger selection plus a list of additional items available for breakfast (additional cost).

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
I styed there for a weekend in February. The rooms are nice and quiet, and the pool/wellness area downstairs is really confidential and pretty.
On the down side, the curtains in the bedroom are not 100% blackout so bring your sleeping mask. The bathroom shower door is not leakproof which i had the bad surprise to discover when i took my first shower in, and there is no ventilation in there so it gets really humid.
I had a couple of minor issues with the front desk: i requested an iron which never came (when I called to remind them an hour later, they had forgotten...) and since there is no concierge, the staff make no effort to give any kind of valuable advice. They were unable to help us on several simple information requests like a good restaurant nearby or a place to buy wine (spoiler alert, we found both within less than 300 meters of the hotel) and we were speaking french. Before us was a couple of Russian people and the staff was completely unable to even understand them, and they made no effort to try to communicate, like to use google translate or something. It was obvious they had absolutely no interest to go out of their way to provide acceptable service.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We just got back from Paris and the Le Metro, and we had a wonderful time! The hotel staff was so accommodating! Even with when we asked for an American size (large) coffee! LOL! Room was very small but very nice furnishings! Location was great, 5 minute walk to the Metro, and 15 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower. Lots of great Bristo's very close to the hotel. Kahina and Sara were so helpful with the Metro! They helped me map out our Metro stops for our tours everyday! Really loved this hotel, and would recommend! Again the room was very small but it was two woman so we made it work. But if you are traveling with a big man you might want to spring for the suite!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Right in the 16th arrondissement, this hotel is a blend of old world charm and modern amenities. We had a magnificent view of The Eiffel tower during day and enjoyed the magical night lighting as well which was a treat! The Arc de triumph is also a walk away so it is very well located ( there is a pharnacy right next to it as well) with Place de mexico across the road. I loved living next to typical french apartments and observing the parisian lifestyle as well as boutiques which are also next door.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Perfect location for a very elegant stay. Very helpful and welcoming staff, with a swimming pool, hammer, great breakfast/lunch/dinner menus, a conference room with a view to die for...all at the heart of the 16th arrondissement. What more would you want?

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: We spent several days at the end of December and beginning of January 2019 at this beautiful and well-run hotel in the 16th arrondissement near the Eiffel Tower. A good example of the fantastic service provided by Kahina at the front desk was that when we arrived late in the afternoon in our rental car, and did not know where to park while we checked in, she came out to the circle and took care of the car for us. Every time we entered or exited the hotel we were greeted by name. Each time we needed to get a new key (which happens repeatedly when you have four kids and multiple rooms) the front desk staff accommodated with kindness and understanding. The location was a good home base for our touring and we were able to find restaurants always within walking distance. There are several grocers, wine and cheese shops in the surrounding blocks, providing snacks. Continental breakfast in the hotel each morning was an assortment of bread and pastries, yogurt, fresh juice, coffee, hot chocolate, or tea. The rooms were clean, spacious and well-appointed. Ours had a tub and a large rainhead shower. It also had a sitting room and a separate bedroom. This hotel also has a pool, which was fun for our youngest traveler. Overall, Kahina and the staff at Le Metropolitan provided us with an excellent experience that only enhanced our visit to Paris. I hope we are able to visit again soon!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Our weeklong stay at Le Metropolitan during the Christmas holidays was absolutely wonderful! This property is perfect for those who prefer an intimate feel, a quiet yet convenient location, and a clean, well-appointed room. We had stayed at Le Metropolitan in summer 2017 before it became part of the Marriott chain, and I am pleased that it has not lost any of its charm.

This time, we stayed in a deluxe room. Though small, it had a nice sofa for lounging, and the bathroom was a good size with a rain shower.
