Last time, we had a junior suite which was amazing and well worth the extra cost. We’d book that again next time, and perhaps one day, a suite with the Eiffel Tower view!

While the location is great (love the 16th Arrondissement!) and the rooms are lovely, it’s the service that makes this hotel stand out. Kahina, the concierge, made us feel welcome even before our arrival. She was warm, courteous, and efficient in handling our special requests via email and always greeted us by name during our stay. All the front-desk staff were terrific, and housekeeping did a great job as well.

Service in the restaurant during breakfast is less even, but we didn’t mind as we just needed a quick bite before starting out our day. If you’re gluten intolerant, gluten-free bread and madeleines are available in lieu of the regular breads and pastries. Each room has an espresso maker which was great, but as a tea drinker, a water kettle would be nice to have (they may provide that on request). There’s also a few grocery stores and lots of wonderful food shops nearby for snacks, wine, cheese, chocolates, etc.

Can’t wait for our next visit!

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: They were very helpful about places to go and things to see. More important, the hotel gave us a cell phone that had an app that updated transit options, which was important given that the Yellow Vests were out one day when we were there. Great neighborhood restaurant recommendations, too.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
Both the service and facilities at this hotel are outstanding. In a great residential location in the 16th, the hotel is very small and offers superb personal service. Kahina at the front desk is particularly helpful.

To accommodate my wife and two young daughters, we booked two rooms. The hotel placed us in a beautiful top floor junior suite with connecting king room. With only a handful of rooms per floor, we had an incredible amount of privacy. The decor is sleek and modern in an extremely tasteful manner.

The hotel is extremely well located only a block from the trocadero and incredible access to and views of the Eiffel Tower. One of the great pleasures of staying here is being able to do a morning jog from the hotel to the base of the Eiffel Tower in a little more than 5 minutes.

This is an especially good choice for travelers who have visited Paris before and have experienced the larger centrally located hotels. This little gem of a hotel in one of Paris’ best neighborhoods is a place that warrants repeat visits.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews:
I stay at Le Metropolitan almost every time I visit Paris.
The hotel is charming, with comfortable beds and basic amenities and a complementary mobile phone that you can use during your stay. Try to get a room with a view. Was upgraded once, the suite is awesome.

Customer service is fantastic, with fast check-in/ check-out and very courteous and helpful staff.

Location is great, walking distance to Trocadéro from which you could connect to practically every corner of the city via subway.

Only downside is breakfast, which I only tried once and wasn’t too impressed. I would go to some bakery or market nearby for more fresh products.

Would definitely come again.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Great staff! A small boutique hotel with small staff. Everyone is very friendly. Only one restaurant and it's not open all the time and room service till midnight. Food is ok but lot of options right around. Two supermarkets right across the street. Rooms are nice but not that big. Great location! Overall I enjoyed the stay a lot.

hotel: Le Metropolitan, Paris Tour Eiffel, a Tribute Portfolio Hotel
reviews: Finally a gourmet restaurant in the neighborhood of Ave Victor Hugo paris 16! Try the Cote de veau -exceptionnel ! Good service and atmosphere! Highly recommended for those who enjoy good food at reasonable prices!
